        "description": {
            "value": "<p>You create a gray storm cloud that pelts creatures with an icy deluge. When you @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.aBQ8ajvEBByv45yz]{Cast the Spell}, a burst of magical hail deals [[/r 2d8 #bludgeoning]] bludgeoning damage and [[/r 2d8 #cold]] cold damage to each creature in the area below the cloud (basic Reflex save). Snow and sleet continue to rain down in the area for the remainder of the spellâ€™s duration, making the area difficult terrain, causing creatures in the storm to be @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.DmAIPqOBomZ7H95W]{Concealed}, and making creatures outside the storm Concealed from those inside the storm. Any creature that ends its turn in the storm takes [[/r 4 #cold]] cold damage. If you Cast this Spell outdoors, you can create two non-overlapping clouds instead of one.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Heightened (+2)</strong> The initial bludgeoning damage and cold damage increase by 1d8 each, and the cold damage creatures take at the end of their turns increases by 2.</p>",
